    "result": {"data":{"strapiPost":{"strapiId":5237,"title":"Harps Acquires The Markets In Louisiana and Mississippi ","topic":"Business","slug":"harps-acquires-the-markets-in-louisiana-and-mississippi","coverImage":{"publicURL":"/static/3dd8d6efeb6b549494b87a8147e39b72/0598c5236aaaecf991dab3217b6e7f7d.JPG"},"photoCredit":"NWA Daily","date":"2022-10-27","content":"<p>This week <a href=\"https://www.supermarketnews.com/retail-financial/harps-food-stores-acquire-markets\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(220, 161, 13);\">Harps Food Stores</a> announced the acquisition of seven stores from <a href=\"https://www.toi.news/food/loy-family-selling-the-markets-to-harps-food-stores-based-in-arkansas-mississippis-best-community-newspaper/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(220, 161, 13);\">The Markets</a> in Louisiana and Mississippi.</p><ul><li><strong>Good things grow</strong>: Founded in Springdale in 1930, Harps is the largest <a href=\"https://talkbusiness.net/2022/10/harps-foods-acquires-seven-stores-in-louisiana-and-mississippi/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(220, 161, 13);\">employee-owned</a> company in Arkansas, currently employing more than 6,800 people at 135 stores across four states.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Minimal change</strong>: The Markets will remain under the same name and its 350+ employees will maintain their jobs if they choose with minimal day to day changes expected.</li></ul><p>Read more about the acquisition <a href=\"https://www.supermarketnews.com/retail-financial/harps-food-stores-acquire-markets\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(220, 161, 13);\">HERE</a>.</p>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"harps-acquires-the-markets-in-louisiana-and-mississippi"}},
